post3: {'mediaType': 2, 'likeCount': 3530, 'commentCount': 16, 'caption': '“Now is the time to understand how climate change is affecting day-to-day life for highlanders in Bhutan. Decreasing snowfall has led to drought, which impacts local growing of barley and vegetables—most of the crops now grow only in greenhouses. We, the highlanders, depend on natural sources of income: cordyceps (mushroom fungus) and various medical herbs. Additionally, in the glacier region, melting ice has increased the volume of flowing rivers, which is impacting biodiversity, washing away farmland and nearly destroying the settlement that is near the river. If we do not address climate change soon, it will become a serious issue that leads to rural-urban migration, unemployment and economic impact.” \n\n@thaileki was one of 7 Bhutanese national athletes at the 2024 Snowman Race: a five-day event tracing 109 miles through some of Bhutan’s most climate-vulnerable regions, including his home village of Laya. Clare Gallagher and @slukenelson joined Leki and 13 others, all of whom were there to witness these harsh climate impacts firsthand and then share the story with the world.', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 193416}

post11:
{'mediaType': 2, 'likeCount': 6126, 'commentCount': 36, 'caption': '“At the high point of the race, just below 18,000 feet, I saw the biggest glacier on the course. Granted, I was sick with altitude, but trust me when I tell you that I think this glacier wanted to eat me.” —Clare Gallagher 

Hallucinations are par for the course in ultramarathons. Often, they’re nonsensical: penguins in the middle of the trail, floating houses, faces in trees. But at the Snowman Race, Clare Gallagher found deep learning in her delirium. 

“This glacier was so mad because our world—the one of overconsumption, fossil fuel extraction, endless development and climate change—is making her melt. I don’t blame her.” 

Situated at the southern end of the Tibetan Plateau, Bhutan is a magnifying glass for climate change. The country’s Himalayan region is home to dozens of glaciers, many of which are shrinking rapidly due to climate change. Meltwater is accumulating into lakes, which eventually burst, flooding the river valleys—and communities—below. The Snowman Race was an opportunity for Gallagher, @slukenelson and 14 other runners to come face-to-face with these disappearing giants and the people they threaten.', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 256765}

bio: Uncovering the world of Patek Philippe, the last independent, family-owned Genevan watch manufacture. Welcome. #PatekTime #patektime
highest_post: {'likeCount': 17607, 'commentCount': 90, 'mediaType': 'Carousel', 'caption': 'The cushion-shaped Ref. 5940 perpetual calendar has a charming 1920s-1930s vintage aesthetic in hand-polished yellow gold with glistening curved flanks that seem to melt imperceptibly into the elegant, tapered lugs. This carefully calculated design was expertly crafted to achieve a sense of grace on the wrist. Visible through the model’s sapphire crystal caseback, the legendary ultra-thin (3.88 mm high) caliber 240 Q movement with a 22k gold minirotor confidently ticks away. Its 275 individual parts power the timepiece’s complex functions and regulate its timekeeping, allowing for an impressive rate of accuracy ranging from just -3 to +2 seconds per day. \n\n#PatekTime', 'contains_in': False, 'viewCount': 0}

post2: {'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 4580, 'commentCount': 26, 'caption': 'The Art Deco-style is reflected throughout the Paris Salons, in harmony between tradition and innovation. post3: {'mediaType': 2, 'likeCount': 1394, 'commentCount': 6, 'caption': "The City of Light has a special significance for Patek Philippe. In 1844, Antoine Norbert de Patek first met Jean Adrien Philippe, in Paris, and a piece of history was made. Over a century later, in 1986, Philippe Stern (then President of Patek Philippe) opened the first Salons outside Geneva on Avenue Montaigne, marking a significant milestone in the company’s history. In 1995, they moved to Place Vendôme, Paris’ most emblematic landmark for 'haute horlogerie' and 'haute joaillerie', where it has remained ever since.\n\n#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeSalons", 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 35322}

post5: {'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 14407, 'commentCount': 86, 'caption': 'Located at 16 New Bond Street since 2014, the London Salon is a light-filled haven of modern Art Deco design. post8:
{'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 9335, 'commentCount': 92, 'caption': 'The Geneva Salons dates back to the ’Belle Époque’ era, when elegance and craftsmanship intertwined. This exquisite space features soaring double-height ceilings that create an airy ambiance, while the walls are adorned with rich dark wood and luxurious leather from Córdoba, exuding sophistication. Illuminated by a majestic original chandelier that captures an essence of timeless beauty. Antique safes, at the rear of the Salon Napoleon III, acquired in 1876, add a touch of historical charm.

Together, these elements create an intimate environment that invites guests to explore and savor the artistry of watchmaking.

The Salons was entirely renovated by specialists in their field to bring the Salon back to its original glory while leading it into the 21st century.

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeSalons', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 0}
post9:
{'mediaType': 2, 'likeCount': 8238, 'commentCount': 44, 'caption': 'The Patek Philippe Geneva Salons could perhaps be called the first among equals of what would become exclusive places around the world dedicated to Patek Philippe. 

It was in 1853 that the company moved to two floors of its current building on the 168 rue du Rhône in Geneva (later to become 41 rue du Rhône), and has far lasted for more than 170 years; the building has become an enduring part of the city landscape.

In 2006, the historic manufacturing headquarters of Patek Philippe has been dedicated to its customers, for whom this hallowed building is a kind of spiritual home known simply as “The Salons”. Today, the Salons connect the past with the present.

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeSalons', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 256442}
post10: {'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 9619, 'commentCount': 63, 'caption': 'An enduringly beautiful form watch, the original ultra-thin self-winding Ref. 5940 in yellow gold, launched in 2012, has an 18k yellow gold cushion-shaped case and a grained, cream-colored dial that perfectly complements the gold hue of the case. The Ref. 5940 was also produced in two white gold versions – with a velvety silvery-white dial released in 2014 and an ebony black opaline dial released in 2015; and in rose gold with a silvery grained dial released in 2017. \n\n#PatekTime', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 0}

Introduced in 1969, the TAG Heuer Monaco quickly became one of the most innovative timepieces\xa0in history. Its bold square shape, left crown, and striking blue dial were revolutionary—unlike anything the world had seen before.

Through the decades, the Monaco has continually evolved, refining its precision, durability, and unmistakable design, while staying true to its legendary racing heritage. With its avant-garde square shape and pioneering Caliber 11 movement, the Monaco embodies the same rebellious spirit as the circuit it’s named after—a timepiece as daring as it is enduring, built with speed, elegance, and relentless precision in every tick.

#TAGHeuer #TAGHeuerMonaco', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 0}

- Up to 40% better fuel economy than non-hybrid models, with a 581-mile total range.

- Improved power from a 2.5L SUBARU BOXER engine and electric motors.

- Standard Subaru Symmetrical All-Wheel Drive.

- A modernized interior with an 11.6-inch multimedia system and a 12.3-inch full digital gauge cluster.

- Available spring 2025, starting at $34,995.

The 2026 Forester Wilderness is their most rugged model yet:

- 9.3 inches of ground clearance with advanced X-MODE for off-road performance.

- Standard Yokohama Geolandar all-terrain tires and StarTex water-resistant upholstery.

- Towing capacity increased to 3,500 pounds and roof rail capacity up to 800 pounds.

- Unique styling inside and out, with upgraded cooling for tougher adventures.

- Available fall 2025.

Subaru is redefining adventure with these models, offering more capability and sustainability while staying true to their outdoorsy roots. post10:
{'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 3, 'commentCount': 1498, 'caption': 'Stasera quella bambina dedica questa canzone al posto che l’ha cresciuta.
A Roma mia.
Alle nostre persone.
A Val Melaina, a V9, al Tufello, a Monte Sacro.
A Talenti, a San Basilio, a Piazza Sempione, a Piazza Monte Gennaro. 
A Gabriella Ferri, alla Magnani, a Sordi, a Califano.
A tutto il cantautorato Italiano.
Alla splendida Elodie, alle nostre storie, “A mano a mano”, alla nostra “Città Folle”.
A tutti i miei ragazzi fuori.
A Kikka, a Fra, alla loro famiglia.
Ai miei turbolenti minorenni.
A Emiano, Mattera, Francesco, Wisky, Fabrizio, Ruben.
A Sandro quando riuscivamo in due a fa’ ‘n piatto de pasta.
A tutti i ragazzi di Val Padana.
A chi non c’è piu. 
A Cesare, a Sabrina.
Al grande vuoto che ci hanno lasciato e
a tutto questo immenso amor,
teppista e vagabondo.
Per noi che moriremo diversi dagli altri.
Per noi che non sapevamo cosa fosse una famiglia. 
Vi devo tutto.
Per sempre noi,
Incoscienti Giovani.

-

Tonight, that girl dedicates this song to the place that raised her.
To my Rome.
To our people.
To Val Melaina, to V9, to Tufello, to Monte Sacro.
To Talenti, to San Basilio, to Piazza Sempione, to Piazza Monte Gennaro.
To Gabriella Ferri, to Magnani, to Sordi, to Califano.
To all the Italian singer‐songwriters.
To the splendid Elodie, to our stories, “A mano a mano”, to our “Città Folle”.
To all my boys out there.
To Kikka, to Fra, to their family.
To my turbulent minors.
To Emiano, Mattera, Francesco, Wisky, Fabrizio, Ruben.
To Sandro, for when the two of us managed to make a plate of pasta.
To all the boys of Val Padana.
To those who are no longer here.
To Cesare, to Sabrina.
To the huge void they left us, and to this immense love, punk and vagabond.
For us, who will die different from the rest.
For us, who never knew what a family was.
I owe you everything.
Forever us,
Incoscienti Giovani.

#Sanremo2025 #DolceGabbana', 'isCollaborated': True, 'viewCount': 0}

Incoscienti Giovani.

post3:
{'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 3, 'commentCount': 154, 'caption': 'Designing a Hypercar means mastering the invisible.

Air is both a challenge and an opportunity—it must be penetrated effortlessly, yet harnessed to generate the downforce that keeps the car firmly planted.

After all, you would not want to see a Pagani take off. At speeds exceeding 300 km/h, it is not as far-fetched as it might seem!

Some call this balance a "compromise"; we call it a "challenge"—one that excites us.

The challenge of achieving the best aerodynamic efficiency while preserving an elegant aesthetic and, in the case of the Pagani Utopia, a design that celebrates purity and fluidity. A dance between beauty and function, where air is not an enemy to fight, but an ally to embrace.

📷 Courtesy of: @dupontregistry @grubbsphotography

#Pagani #PaganiAutomobili #PaganiUtopia #dupontregistry', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 0}
post4:
{'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 3, 'commentCount': 151, 'caption': 'Many consider the Zonda F the most romantic Pagani of all time—a poem in motion that tells the endless love story between engineering and beauty.

Its naturally aspirated V12 pulses like a fervent heartbeat, while its flowing lines evoke a dancer’s grace, merging sensuality with elegance in a design that defies time.

Over the years, it has raced with breathtaking fervor, shattering records like the Nürburgring Nordschleife lap time—a testament to the human spirit’s unyielding drive to surpass limits.

Today, we honor it not just as a car, but as a symbol of everything that makes love eternal: passion, dedication, and the power to make our hearts race faster with every glance.

Happy Valentine’s Day!

This year, The I.C.E. St. Moritz promises double the thrill.
On the frozen lake, the roar of engines will shatter winter’s silence as two Hypercars—each with the purity of a manual gearbox—challenge the immaculate white: the Huayra Epitome and the Utopia Roadster. Handcrafted elegance in motion.

See you on February 21 and 22 at The I.C.E.

In the meantime, enjoy some images from last year’s event.

#Pagani #PaganiAutomobili', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 0}

{'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 3, 'commentCount': 123, 'caption': 'Technology is not just performance. It is the raw, unfiltered thrill of driving.

The Utopia Roadster slices through the streets, its sculpted muscles meet aerodynamic grace.
But the real magic lies in the way it bonds with the driver.

A carbon monocoque that is not just rigid, but precise. Not just light, but alive.

Rigidity sharpens every movement with surgical precision, making you feel the road as if your fingertips could read the asphalt. Lightness translates into agility—a car that surges forward at the slightest touch, responding like a heartbeat.

post7:
{'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 3, 'commentCount': 149, 'caption': 'Easy, right? Just remove the roof, and the Huayra becomes the Roadster.
But you know us. That is not how we think.

We started from scratch to create the Huayra Roadster because every Pagani is born with its own soul. For six years, we imagined, designed, deconstructed, rebuilt, and searched for the perfect form. Then, one day, it came to life before our eyes.

Sculpted lines, even more intense. The front opens in a confident smile, framed by wider wheel arches. The roll bar defines its silhouette, carving it through the air. Every element speaks to aerodynamics, striking the perfect balance between elegance and performance.

And then, there is the true protagonist: the mechanics. No filters, no secrets. Every component is revealed with pride, because in Pagani’s philosophy, nothing is hidden. Every screw, every detail is crafted to be both functional and sublime. Because to us, perfection is not a mystery—it is a commitment.

📷 Courtesy of @KenoZache

#Pagani #PaganiAutomobili #HuayraRoadster', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 0}

⏳ 𝙔𝙀𝘼𝙍 𝟮𝟬𝟬𝟮

In 2002, the Zonda earned its place in the pantheon of ultra-high-performance cars. Revered for its feather-light construction and meticulous design, it mastered contrasts: raw power with drivability, advanced technology with craftsmanship—all for pure driving pleasure. 

🇬🇧
«Our Car of the Year is the Pagani Zonda C12S, and though some of us might have felt a tad uneasy about giving the gong to a car that costs the best part of a quarter of a million pounds, when you were sat behind the wheel and being submerged in all the sensations of driving quickly on a great stretch of road, there was no doubt. No doubt at all.»

(Peter Tomalin, Car of the Year 2001, “evo”, 039, January 2002, UK)

🇬🇧
«A new fin has broken the still waters of the supercar pond, swimming with murderous intent towards the silhouette of Ferrari and Lamborghini – and that fin has ‘Pagani’ writ large. The Performance Car of the Year 2002.»

(Tom Ford, Performance Car of the Year, “car”, December 2002, UK)

🇦🇺
«One drive is enough to justify the million-dollar price tag. Seriously. Beautifully built, brilliantly resolved, and so easy to drive, the huge performance is always exploitable.»

(Peter Robinson, Techno Drive, “Wheels Yearbook 02”, 2002, Australia)

🇬🇧
«But the Zonda S, crucially, is the most manageable supercar we have ever driven on the open road.»

(Chris Harris, Autocar Road Test, Pagani Zonda, “Autocar”, 23, 4 June 2002, UK)

🇬🇧

post12:
{'mediaType': 8, 'likeCount': 3, 'commentCount': 205, 'caption': 'Downforce—it is not just a feature; it is our obsession.

The redesigned Imola Roadster’s air vents do more than refresh its aesthetics—they revolutionize performance by extracting heat from the wheel arches, enhancing rear brake cooling, and increasing downforce.

Impeccable road grip transforms aerodynamic force into pure stability, putting full control firmly in your hands. Every curve, every straight, every moment—it is yours to command.

The Imola Roadster does not simply drive—it carves the asphalt with surgical precision. In steady-state cornering, lateral acceleration reaches an extraordinary 2.0 g, with peaks of 2.2 g. Imagine pulling those forces in every sharp turn. Longitudinal deceleration is a staggering 2.2 g, allowing you to stop as sharply as you accelerate.

These numbers are not just statistics—they are the science behind exhilaration. Imagine the asphalt beneath you, the tires gripping like a force of nature, as if the car were tethered to the ground by gravity itself.

At Pagani, exhilaration is not just a feeling. It is a formula, perfected.

#Pagani #PaganiAutomobili #ImolaRoadster', 'isCollaborated': False, 'viewCount': 0}

Suzuki Motor USA, LLC, in partnership with Team Hammer, Inc. is pleased to announce the return of Sean Dylan Kelly to the team for the 2025 MotoAmerica AMA/FIM North American Road Racing season. Kelly will compete in the MotoAmerica Superbike Championship aboard the Suzuki GSX-R1000R, aiming to add another title to his impressive racing résumé.

Now, the 22-year-old Florida native looks to build on that success as he reunites with Team Hammer to challenge for the 2025 MotoAmerica Superbike Championship.

“I’m back with Team Hammer, where I have some of my absolute best racing memories,” said Kelly. “It feels good to be coming back to the team to give it a shot in Superbike. I am excited to see what the Suzuki GSX-R1000R is like now that I have two Moto2 seasons and a year of Superbike under my belt. Clearly the objective is to do the best we can and eventually that means to win races as we put it all together.”

The MotoAmerica Superbike season kicks off Barber Motorsports Park April 5-7.

Cumulative deliveries reached 685,427 as of January 31, 2025.
